import io
import zlib
import struct
def extract_file_from_zip_stream(zip_bytes, filename_to_extract):
    stream = io.BytesIO(zip_bytes)
    while True:
        header = stream.read(4)
        print('len(header)')
        if len(header) < 4:
            break
        # Signature d'en-tête locale de fichier ZIP
        print(header)
        if header != b'PK\x03\x04':
            break
        # Lire l'en-tête locale : 26 octets suivants
        local_file_header = stream.read(26)
        (
            version, flag, compression, mod_time, mod_date,
            crc32, compressed_size, uncompressed_size,
            filename_len, extra_len
        ) = struct.unpack('<HHHHHIIIHH', local_file_header)
        filename = stream.read(filename_len).decode('utf-8')
        stream.read(extra_len)  # ignorer les champs supplémentaires
        # Lire les données compressées
        compressed_data = stream.read(compressed_size)
        print(filename)
        if filename == filename_to_extract:
            # Décompression via zlib (compression DEFLATE = méthode 8)
            if compression == 8:
                decompressed_data = zlib.decompress(compressed_data, -15)  # -15 = raw DEFLATE
                print(f"Contenu de {filename_to_extract} :\n")
                out.write_bytes(decompressed_data)
                return decompressed_data
            else:
                print(f"Compression {compression} non prise en charge")
    print(f"Fichier {filename_to_extract} non trouvé dans l'archive")
